# Steering — Coding standards (cross-cutting, agent-wide)

Project-specific overrides to general language conventions. Loaded into every Claude session for this repo.

## Format

- Indent: <2 spaces | 4 spaces | tabs>
- Line length: <80 | 100 | 120>
- Trailing newline at EOF: <yes | no>

## Naming

- File names: <snake_case | kebab-case | camelCase>
- Types: <PascalCase>
- Variables: <camelCase | snake_case>
- Constants: <SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE>

## Imports

- <Group order: stdlib → third-party → internal | alphabetical | other>
- <No wildcards | wildcards-allowed-in-tests>

## Error handling

- <Errors must be wrapped with context | bare returns OK>
- <Panics permitted in <listed_cases> only>

## Logging

- <Structured (slog/zap) only | printf OK in scripts>
- <No PII in logs (see security-baseline.md for the regex list)>

## Testing

- <Table-driven preferred over single-case tests>
- <Test files live alongside source (foo_test.go)>
- <Coverage threshold: NN% per package>
